3. LEGAL DISTINCTION FROM PRIOR ART (US PATENT 12392583B2)
This work is legally and technically distinct from the "Body safety device with visual sensing" described in US Patent 12392583B2 (Assignee: GovernmentGPT Inc.).
*   Crowd OS utilizes STATIONARY INFRASTRUCTURE sensors (clamped to poles/walls) to detect crowd fluid dynamics.
*   Crowd OS does NOT utilize body-worn visual sensors, cameras, or sensors integrated into tactical gear/vests.
*   Any attempt to conflate this infrastructure-based system with body-worn tactical patents is rejected as factually incorrect.

4. THIRD-PARTY ATTRIBUTION (PHYSIOKIT)
Portions of the wearable hardware design are adapted from the open-source "PhysioKit" architecture.
*   Original Work: Joshi, J., Wang, K., & Cho, Y. (2023). PhysioKit: An Open-Source, Low-Cost Physiological Computing Toolkit. Sensors, 23(19), 8244.
*   License: CC BY 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
*   Note: The PhysioKit framework is used solely for the physiological sensing module. The Crowd OS mesh networking, "Rapid Reunion" triangulation, and "Density Crusher" logic remain proprietary to Prasurjya Deka.
